    "body": "### Problem\n\nAdding `inline` extmark to the buffer and then adding `overlay` extmark on top of it does not detect the `inline` extmark when the line starts at 0 column. When the starting column is > 0, it works fine.\r\nThe images below will explain it better.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a test file: `echo \"- First item\\n  - Second item\" > test.txt`\r\n2. Create a `repro.lua` file with this content:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('repro')\r\nlocal bufnr = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\r\n\r\n-- Add inline extmarks to both lines\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, 0, 0, {\r\n  virt_text = {{'  '}},\r\n  virt_text_pos = 'inline',\r\n})\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, 1, 0, {\r\n  virt_text = {{'  '}},\r\n  virt_text_pos = 'inline',\r\n})\r\n\r\n-- Add overlay extmarks to both lines\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, 0, 0, {\r\n  end_col = 1,\r\n  virt_text = {{'x'}},\r\n  virt_text_pos = 'overlay',\r\n  hl_mode = 'combine',\r\n})\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, 1, 2, {\r\n  end_col = 3,\r\n  virt_text = {{'x'}},\r\n  virt_text_pos = 'overlay',\r\n  hl_mode = 'combine',\r\n})\r\n```\r\n3. Open the test file `nvim --clean test.txt`\r\n4. source the repro file `:luafile repro.lua`\r\n\r\nResult:\r\n![screenshot_2024_02_18_11_50_32](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/1782860/65c715b5-f9a1-4f28-b596-e59cd831dc4a)\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFirst line should have overlay extmark at correct position:\r\n\r\n![screenshot_2024_02_18_11_51_19](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/1782860/b627bf10-885d-423f-9c2d-daa017930cd0)\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2388+gb12d193b4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhttps://github.com/MordechaiHadad/bob",
